A matrix is a two-dimensional array of elements arranged in rows and columns 
It is represented as a rectangular grid, with each element at the intersection 
a row and a columns

Key Concepts:

Rows: Horizontal lines of elements in a matrix
Columns: Vertical lines of elements in a matrix
Dimensions: The number of rows and columns in a matrix (3x4, 3 rows 4 columns)
Element Access: Elements can be accessed using row and column indices (M[2][2], refers to the element in row 2, column 2)

